<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CGood quarter,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Ccongr=
atulations=E2=80=9D and similar plaudits are drying up on quarterly earning=
s calls for S&amp;P 500 companies, setting up 2023 for the biggest such ann=
ual decline since the Great Recession. The drop is even more pronounced whe=
n compared with the pandemic era, running 35% below the average pace in the=
 previous three years. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The slump in congratulatory remarks may point =
to increasingly concerned investors heading into 2024 as the risk of inflat=
ion remains sticky, potentially putting more pressure on policymakers. ...<=
/p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And senior executives do care whether or not W=
all Street research firms pat them on the back. =E2=80=9COne hundred percen=
t, we take notice of it,=E2=80=9D said Gina Mastantuono, chief financial of=
ficer of ServiceNow Inc. =E2=80=9CWe are very mindful of feedback,=E2=80=9D=
 she said. Santa Clara-based software provider ServiceNow has received over=
 150 plaudits over the last five years, the most among members of the S&amp=
;P 500, though the amount of kudos it received this quarter fell to seven f=
rom 12 a year ago.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a chart, counting =E2=80=9Cgood quart=
er,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Cgreat quarter,=E2=80=9D =E2=80=9Ccongrats=E2=80=9D an=
d =E2=80=9Ccongratulations=E2=80=9D by quarter back through 2019. I wonder =
if anyone trades on this as a signal. Not, like, for the stock, but for mac=
ro trading; is a downturn in =E2=80=9Cgreat quarter guys=E2=80=9D a leading=
 indicator of recession? Of recovery? Anyway I wrote yesterday that the obv=
ious solution, for conference calls, is for investors and analysts to use r=
obots to ask the questions, and for companies to use robots to answer them.=
 That probably solves this problem: Maybe the analyst-robots would not say =
=E2=80=9Cgreat quarter guys,=E2=80=9D but the executive-robots would not be=
 offended.</p>
